An urgent search has been launched for a mum and her young daughter after they vanished four days ago. There are concerns for Sabrina Bradshaw, 29, and Taylor Kelly, 10, after they disappeared on March 25. The pair, from West Sussex, were spotted 140 miles from home on Sunday evening in Suffolk. A sighting was made in Aldeburgh at Moot Hall, a Tudor building which has a museum inside. Sabrina has blonde hair and was last seen wearing a cream fur waistcoat, light blue jeans. Taylor is described as having shoulder length dark brown hair. It is thought they are using a black Renault Kadjar vehicle with the number plate LX67 KFJ. Anyone with information is urged to come forward to Suffolk Police. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.